sub = ['Goal Scored','Ball Possession %',
       'Attempts', 'On-Target', 'Off-Target', 'Blocked', 'Corners', 'Offsides',
       'Free Kicks', 'Saves', 'Pass Accuracy %', 'Passes',
       'Distance Covered (Kms)', 'Fouls Committed', 'Yellow Card']
temp = df[sub]
# Normalize Tournament Data(Min-Max Scale)
data_norm = (temp - temp.mean()) / (temp.max() - temp.min())
plot1 = sns.boxplot(data = data_norm)
plot1.set_xticklabels(sub, rotation=90, ha="center")
plot1.set(xlabel='M√©tricas',ylabel='Total Normalizado')
plot1.set_title('Boxsplot de m√©tricas dos jogos da copa do mundo 2018')

Total On-target, Off-target e blocked por seleções¶

In [47]:
group_attempt = df.groupby('Team')['On-Target','Off-Target','Blocked'].sum().reset_index()

# Modificando o dataframe para plotar os valores
group_attempt_sorted = group_attempt.melt('Team', var_name='Target', value_name='Value')

plot1 = sns.barplot(x="Team", y="Value", hue="Target", data=group_attempt_sorted)
plot1.set_xticklabels(group_attempt_sorted['Team'], rotation=90, ha="center")
plot1.set(xlabel='Sele√ß√µes',ylabel='Total de Tentativas de Gol')
plot1.set_title('Total On-Target, Off-Target e Blocked')

In [64]:
mask = np.zeros_like(df.corr(), dtype=np.bool)
mask[np.triu_indices_from(mask)] = True

plt.subplots(figsize = (20,20))
sns.heatmap(df.corr(), 
            annot=True,
            mask = mask,
            cmap = 'RdBu_r',
            linewidths=0.1, 
            linecolor='white',
            vmax = .9,
            square=True)
plt.title("Correlations Among Features", y = 1.03,fontsize = 7)

Radar Plot da Final¶

In [60]:
'''
import plotly
import plotly.plotly as py
import plotly.graph_objs as go
import numpy as np

# R√≥tulos para o Radar plot

labels=np.array(['Goal Scored', 'Attempts', 'Corners', 'Offsides', 'Free Kicks', 'Saves', 'Fouls Committed', 'Yellow Card'])

# Dados da final entre France e Croacia

data1=df.loc[126,labels].values
data2=df.loc[127,labels].values

# Criando um radar plot usando plotly

plotly.offline.init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

data = [
    go.Scatterpolar(
      r = data1,
      theta = labels,
      mode = 'lines',
      fill = 'toself',
      name = 'France'
    ),

    go.Scatterpolar(
      r = data2,
      theta = labels,
      mode = 'lines',
      fill = 'toself',
      name = 'Croatia'
    )
]

layout = go.Layout(
    title='Finals - "France vs Croatia"',
    polar = dict(
        radialaxis = dict(
          visible = True,
          range = [0, 20]
        )
      ),
    showlegend = True
)

fig = go.Figure(data=data, layout=layout)
plotly.offline.iplot(fig)
'''
